{"word":"Βαραββᾶς","slug":"Βαραββᾶς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>Βαραββᾶς, ᾶ, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Aram.\">Aram.</a> ‘son of Abbas’; a common name] Barabbas, the criminal in the passion story <b><a href='B:470 27:20'>Mt 27:20f</a>, 26</b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ par.\">par.</a> <b><a href='B:470 27:16'>Mt 27:16f</a>,</b> according to old tradition, records his full name as <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Ἰησοῦς\">Ἰησοῦς</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:Βαραββᾶς\">Βαραββᾶς</a></el> <i>Joshua Barabbas.</i> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:βάρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Βαράκ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}